Payne Zero attribution notice
=============================

Payne Zero implements the numerical structure and scientific data conventions
of the Kurucz ATLAS12 and SYNTHE programs. Please cite the relevant Kurucz
programs and line-data publications when using this work.

The immediate implementation and validation lineage is pyKurucz:

  Elliot M. Kim and Yuan-Sen Ting, pyKurucz: A Pure Python Reimplementation of
  Kurucz ATLAS12 and SYNTHE for Self-Consistent Stellar Atmospheres and Spectra
  (2026), https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11693

pyKurucz is MIT licensed, copyright (c) 2026 Elliot M. Kim and Yuan-Sen Ting.

The representative APOGEE line-spread-function builder follows the public
jobovy/apogee implementation, copyright (c) 2013 Jo Bovy, distributed under the
BSD 3-Clause License. APOGEE survey products are provided by SDSS. The solar
and Arcturus calibration overlays were derived from the NSO/Kitt Peak solar FTS
atlas and the Hinkle, Wallace & Livingston Arcturus atlas. The distributed
overlays contain fitted corrections, not atlas spectra.

Payne Zero-authored source code and generated model products are covered by the
repository LICENSE. Upstream programs, catalogs, tables, and survey products
retain their original attribution and terms.
